<div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">Request for Change:<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">What: Add support for Mellanox Technologies&#8217; next-generation non-blocking collectives, code-named &#8220;libhcoll&#8221;. This comes in the form of a new &#8220;hcoll&#8221; component to the &#8220;coll&#8221; framework. &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Where: Trunk and 1.7 <o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">When: July 1<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Why: In support of MPI 3, Mellanox Technologies will make available its next generation collectives library, &#8220;libhcoll&#8221;, &nbsp;in MOFED 2.0 releases and higher starting in the late 2013 timeframe. &#8220;Libhcoll&#8221; adds support for truly asynchronous
 non-blocking collectives on supported HCAs (Connect X-3 and higher) via Mellanox Technologies&#8217; CORE-<i>Direct</i> technology. &#8220;Libhcoll&#8221; also adds support for hierarchical collectives and features a highly scalable infrastructure battle tested and proven on
 some of the world&#8217;s largest HPC systems. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
